    ],
    "notes": "Detection logic for T1055.013 KernelCallbackTable/Ctrl-C handler injection should combine: (1) EID 10 with GrantedAccess containing 0x1fffff or 0x0838 (PROCESS_VM_WRITE+VM_OPERATION) from a non-system process targeting conhost.exe or other console-attached GUI processes, AND (2) source process executable path under user AppData or Temp. The EID 8 CreateRemoteThread into conhost.exe or csrss.exe from a non-system process is a high-confidence signal on its own. Benign discriminators: signed binary path (Program Files vs AppData), SYSTEM vs interactive user, lower GrantedAccess bits. Filter MsMpEng.exe, CrashPad, and known EDR processes by path to reduce FPs."
  },
